{{italic title}} {{Infobox artwork | title = The Holy Family with Three Hares | image = The Holy Family with Three Hares - Albrecht Dürer c. 1496.jpg | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | artist = Albrecht Dürer | year = c. 1496 <!-- If after 1583 CE, use {{start date|YYYY}} --> | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | type = [[Woodcut]] | height_metric = 38.6 <!-- (i.e. in metric units) --> | width_metric = 28 | metric_unit = cm <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = in <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> }}
'''''The Holy Family with Three Hares''''' is a c. 1496 [[woodcut]] by German artist [[Albrecht Dürer]] (1471–1528). It depicts the [[Christianity|Christian]] [[Holy Family]] of [[Mary, mother of Jesus|Mary]], [[St Joseph|Joseph]], and the [[infant Jesus]], in an [[Hortus conclusus|enclosed garden]], symbolizing Mary's virginity. The infant Jesus is reading from what is very probably a book of scripture, representing his close connection with the Word of God, not only because in Christianity he fulfills the [[Old Testament]] prophecy of a [[messiah]], but also because in some Christian traditions Jesus has been described as the word of God.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Catholic Church|title=Catechism of the Catholic Church|date=2000|publisher=Vatican: Libreria Editrice Vaticana|page=Section 2, Paragraph 1|edition=2nd}}</ref>
